The paper deals with matrix completion and low-rank optimization problems, which are commonly studied in the machine learning and optimization communities. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves theoretical analysis of the algorithm, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The algorithmic aspect of the paper could also make it relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
